    "question_id" : 16243580,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Assert by exception message:</p>\n\n<pre><code>    try {\n        MyAgent.getNameByNode(\"d\");\n    } catch (Exception e) {\n        Assert.assertEquals(\"Failed to fetch data.\", e.getMessage());\n    }\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7792408,
      "reputation" : 520,
      "user_id" : 5894853,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/orI5A.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "JediCate",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5894853/jedicate"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1531805110,
    "creation_date" : 1531805110,
    "answer_id" : 51373751,
    "question_id" : 16243580,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Or if your exception is thrown from the constructor of a class: </p>\n\n<pre><code>@Rule\npublic ExpectedException exception = ExpectedException.none();\n\n@Test\npublic void myTest() {    \n\n    exception.expect(MyException.class);\n    CustomClass myClass= mock(CustomClass.class);\n    doThrow(new MyException(\"constructor failed\")).when(myClass);  \n\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 519017,
      "reputation" : 1602,
      "user_id" : 2468458,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 85,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/FTZQE.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Rodrigo Oliveira",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2468458/rodrigo-oliveira"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 18,
    "last_activity_date" : 1548693865,
    "creation_date" : 1548693865,
    "answer_id" : 54406590,
    "question_id" : 16243580,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Use <a href=\"https://static.javadoc.io/org.mockito/mockito-core/2.23.4/org/mockito/Mockito.html#12\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Mockito's doThrow</a> and then catch the desired exception to assert it was thrown later.</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Test\npublic void fooShouldThrowMyException() {\n    // given\n    val myClass = new MyClass();\n    val arg = mock(MyArgument.class);\n    doThrow(MyException.class).when(arg).argMethod(any());\n    Exception exception = null;\n\n    // when\n    try {\n        myClass.foo(arg);\n    } catch (MyException t) {\n        exception = t;\n    }\n\n    // then\n    assertNotNull(exception);\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 19804202,
      "reputation" : 331,
      "user_id" : 14504459,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/k9a0U.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Chetan Botre",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/14504459/chetan-botre"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 20,
    "last_activity_date" : 1677706574,
    "last_edit_date" : 1677706574,
    "creation_date" : 1609753597,
    "answer_id" : 65560548,
    "question_id" : 16243580,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I think this should do it for you.</p>\n<pre><code>assertThrows(someException.class,\n()-&gt; mockedServiceReference.someMethod(param1,parme2,..));\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 26833698,
      "reputation" : 81,
      "user_id" : 20421268,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/73a4d9dea6624d9771f4900c6f3dff23?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
